# Styling Conventions

## Tailwind CSS v4

- No `tailwind.config.ts` â€” configuration lives in `app/globals.css` using `@theme`
- Use CSS variables for colors and theming (light/dark mode via `.dark` class)
- Use `tw-animate-css` for animation utilities

## Class Management

- Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge conditional/dynamic classes
- Use `cva` from `class-variance-authority` for multi-variant component styles
- Use `clsx` patterns inside `cn()` for conditional classes:

```tsx
cn("base-class", condition && "conditional-class", props.className)
```

## Color System

Uses shadcn/ui CSS variable naming:
- `--background`, `--foreground` for base colors
- `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--accent`, `--destructive` for semantic colors
- Each has a `-foreground` counterpart for text on that color
- Reference as Tailwind classes: `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, etc.
